name: INStartWorkoutIntentResponseCode
desc: Constants that indicate the response state.

items.name: case unspecified
items.desc: A response code that indicates an unknown state.

items.name: case ready
items.desc: A response code that indicates app readiness.

items.name: case continueInApp
items.desc: A response code that indicates your app extension is ready to transfer control to the app to start the workout.

items.name: case success
items.desc: A response code that indicates your app succeeded.

items.name: case handleInApp
items.desc: A response code that indicates you want to handle the intent in your app instead.

items.name: case failure
items.desc: A response code that indicates you were unable to start the specified workout.

items.name: case failureRequiringAppLaunch
items.desc: A response code that indicates the user must launch your app to start the workout.

items.name: case failureOngoingWorkout
items.desc: A response code that indicates a workout is already in progress, so another can’t start.

items.name: case failureNoMatchingWorkout
items.desc: A response code that indicates you didn’t find the specified workout.
